# Definitions

analysis_path = os.path.dirname(os.getcwd())

regions = ['accumbens', 'cerebellum', 'mPFC', 'OFC', 'frontal_cortex', 'hippocampus', 'striatum', 'thalamus', 'visual_cortex', 'whole_brain']


def group_allocation (row):
    if row['Treatment_Group_#'] == 1:
        return 'Veh'
    if row['Treatment_Group_#'] == 2:
        return 'Har'
    if row['Treatment_Group_#'] == 3:
        return 'DMT'
    if row['Treatment_Group_#'] == 4:
        return 'Har + DMT'

df['Treatment_Group'] = df.apply(lambda row: group_allocation(row), axis=1)

def plot_region_names (row1):
    if row1['variable'] == 'accumbens':
        return 'NAc'
    if row1['variable'] == 'visual_cortex':
        return 'visual cortex'
In [9]:
df_melted = pd.melt(df, id_vars =['Rat #', 'Treatment_Group',	'Treatment_Group_#',	'Weight [kg]',	'StudyDate [date_time]',	'Time [seconds]'], value_vars =regions)
df_melted = df_melted[(df_melted.variable != 'whole_brain') & (df_melted.variable != 'frontal_cortex')] 

df_melted.loc[df_melted['variable'] == 'accumbens', 'variable'] = 'NAc'
df_melted.loc[df_melted['variable'] == 'visual_cortex', 'variable'] = 'visual cortex'
In [10]:
sns.set(style="ticks", context="talk", rc={"figure.figsize":(30, 15)})

g = sns.boxplot(x='variable', y='value', data=df_melted, 
                order=['mPFC', 'OFC', 'visual cortex', 'hippocampus', 'NAc', 'striatum', 'thalamus', 'cerebellum'],
                hue='Treatment_Group', hue_order=['Veh', 'Har', 'DMT', 'Har + DMT'], showmeans=True, meanprops={"marker": "+",
                       "markeredgecolor": "black",
                       "markersize": "10"}, palette='flare_r', width=.8, boxprops={'alpha': 0.7}) 


old_len_collections = len(g.collections)
sns.stripplot(data=df_melted, x="variable", y="value", 
              order=['mPFC', 'OFC', 'visual cortex', 'hippocampus', 'NAc', 'striatum', 'thalamus', 'cerebellum'],
              hue='Treatment_Group', hue_order=['Veh', 'Har', 'DMT', 'Har + DMT'], ax=g, palette='flare_r', dodge=True) 
            
for dots in g.collections[old_len_collections:]:
    dots.set_offsets(dots.get_offsets() + np.array([-0.05, 0]))

sns.despine()

# Get the handles and labels. For this example it'll be 2 tuples of length 4 each.
handles, labels = g.get_legend_handles_labels()

# When creating the legend, only use the first two elements to effectively remove the last two.
l = plt.legend(handles[0:4], labels[0:4], bbox_to_anchor=(1.0, 1.0), loc=1, borderaxespad=0.)
for handle in l.legendHandles:
    handle.set_alpha(0.7)

g.set_ylabel('whole-brain normalized SUV', fontsize=16)
g.set_xlabel(None)

#rasterized needed for .eps to account for transparency (that comes with the confidence intervals of the regression line)
fig = g.get_figure()
fig.set_rasterized(True)
fig.savefig(f'{analysis_path}/plots_for_paper/PET_regions_plot_wb_norm.eps', dpi=300, format='eps')
fig.savefig(f'{analysis_path}/plots_for_paper/PET_regions_plot_wb_norm.png')
